><br>  Posts: 9<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 12:31:13 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.serve.com/adc/LOS/glasya_face_60x60.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Using fire pet against fire MOBs?</span><hr size=1> I was on a raid recently and decided to use a fire pet against Nagafen only to be told by other mages that I should be using water or air; and demanded I resummon.<br>
<br>
My point is that fire pet is immune to fire attacks and Nagafen's AoE fire attacks will be ineffective against the pet which can continue to deal melee damage.<br>
<br>
Does this make sense?<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/ulorendeldaywalker.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Lorendel Daywalker</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/globalBlack.gif BORDER=0 HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 56<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 12:51:39 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eqforge.com/profiles/4532.jpg height=151 width=112></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using fire pet against fire MOBs?</span><hr size=1> Since my first Nagafen raid, I have used a fire pet. That AoE fire spell of his is nasty. As far as I can tell, even 49 pets are too low to really land a spell on Naggy anyway, so the fire resist is the important thing. <br>
Neh'Ashiir has a bad AoE fire spell as well, Really difficult without a bunch of fire pets...<br>
<br>
Lorendel Daywalker<br>
Level 50 mage of the Mithril Heart Brigade<br>
The Tribunal <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub6.ezboard.com/uextra411.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Extra411</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Elementalist</span><br>  Posts: 47<br> <font color=#333333>(1/5/01 7:07:49 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=153.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://www.geocities.com/extra411/magician6.jpg height=195 width=170></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Using fire pet against fire MOBs?</span><hr size=1> I definitely agree using a firepet on those things aren't bad...<br>
<br>
Just like a few days ago when everyone is killing the huge fire elmenetal thing in BW for the cleric epic quest, every mage used the firepet. Immunity to fire is very good, and it's a LOT more useful than the pet's nuke not able to hit.<br>
