<br>
With all the battle spam, I couldn't really catch what dmg my pet was doing, but in the end my pet got the killing blow that brought Naggy tumbling down to his death bed.  Our caster charge was called at Naggy's 30% health mark, but with Naggy's aoe fear coming, pets were agroing and going in the entire time.  49 fire lived throughout the entire battle and obviously was doing his share of dmg if he got the killing blow/cast.<br>
<br>
Don't worry about everything that everyone else says.  Everyone has different opinions about what to do and not do.  Use your own head and do what YOU think is best.  That afterall is what makes us unique and ultimately makes some better than others as well as giving us all experiences to learn from.  Against Naggy, it really isn't going to mean success or failure of the raid no matter which pet you summon. <p><img src=http://www.geocities.com/kimmi_sc/teldiva_grimleux.jpg>
